owl:Ontology.dc:title: RaDiPO: Rare Disease Proteins Ontology
owl:Ontology.rdfs:comment: Course: Semantic Technologies, Master's in Computational Biology, UPM

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Abilities, task and activities a patient has limitations doing.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Ability_affected

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Human processes or metabolic rutes the protein is involved in. The ids and names are terms from the Gene Ontology.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Biological_process

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: These are drugs with a biological origin. This term includes vaccines, blood components, allergenics, somatic cells, gene therapies, tissues, recombinant therapeutic protein, and living cells used in cell therapy.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Biotech

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Location of a cell where the protein is located. The ids and names are terms from the Gene Ontology.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Cellular_component

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Genetic technical term used to describe the clinical items included in the nomenclature of rare diseases. The id is ORPHAcode.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Clinical_entity

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: The degree to which the ability is affected in the patient.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Degree_of_severity

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: The functional consequences of a disorder are divided into different abilities, task, and activities of the everyday life. Disability involves limitation or restriction in a task.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Disability

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A disorder can be a disease, a symdrom or an anomaly.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Disorder

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A molecular compound that is used as a treatment for a disease involving a protein. The ids and names are from the DrugBank.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Drug

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: An enzyme is a protein that has catalytic activity and a metabolic pathway.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Enzyme

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: The drug is either in experimental phase, approved or withdrawn
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Experimental_phase

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Description of the protein function(s). The names and ids are terms from the Gene Ontology. The description is obtained from Uniprot.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Function

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A group of disorder is a set of disorder that have some properties in common.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Group_of_disorders

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Weather the ability is lost by the pacient over the course of a disease or not.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Loss_of_ability

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A protein is a biological molecule encoded by a gene. The ids and names are retrieved from Uniprot.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Protein

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: This type of protein usually regulates some process in the cell or binds to DNA or RNA to regulate the transcription or translation of a protein.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Regulator

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Low molecular weight drugs (900 daltons) which are produced by chemical synthesis. These drugs have well defined structures and chemical properties. In DrugBank, some drugs larger than 900 daltons are considered small molecule drugs (such as monomers: ribo- or deoxyribonucleotides, amino acids, and monosaccharides).
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Small_molecule

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A subtype of disorder is a especific type of disorder that can be either clinical, etiological or hisotpahtological.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Subtype_of_disorder

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: The symptoms and sign of a disorder are annotated with Human Phenotype Ontology terms.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Symptom

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Period of time the functional consequence/disability is present in the life of the patient.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Temporality

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A protein that can transport a molecule or group of molecules.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Transporter
